.TH HOLBERTONSCHOOL-PRINTF 1 "July 2024" "1.0" "holbertonschool-printf"
.SH NAME
holbertonschool-printf \- Custom implementation of the printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B holbertonschool-printf
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFORMAT\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B holbertonschool-printf
command is a custom implementation of the C standard library function
.B printf.
This program is designed to demonstrate the ability to handle formatted output
in a controlled environment, such as a coding bootcamp or educational context.

The tool supports a subset of the standard
.B printf
features and is intended for educational purposes to help users understand the
internal workings of formatted output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display this help message and exit.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.B -f, --format \fIFORMAT\fR
Specify the format string to be used for output.
.TP
.B -a, --argument \fIARGUMENT\fR
Provide additional arguments to be formatted according to the format string.
.SH EXAMPLES
Print a formatted string to standard output:
.IP
.B holbertonschool-printf "Hello, %s!\n" "world"
.PP
Display version information:
.IP
.B holbertonschool-printf --version
.PP
Show help information:
.IP
.B holbertonschool-printf --help
.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B holbertonschool-printf
command returns an exit status of 0 upon success. If an error occurs, it
returns a non-zero exit status.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Arnaud and Ema.
